# =============================================================
# .gitignore — final / publication-ready configuration
# =============================================================
# Strategy: commit every deliverable (responses, extractions,
# enriched data, judge outputs, scores, figures, human ratings,
# the progress-report PDF). Ignore only the large binary caches
# that can be regenerated, plus standard dev cruft and secrets.
# =============================================================

# =============================================================
# Secrets and environment
# =============================================================
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# =============================================================
# Python build artifacts and virtual environments
# =============================================================
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
build/
dist/
.venv/
venv/
env/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# =============================================================
# Caches and databases (large, binary, regenerable from scripts)
# =============================================================
# SQLite caches: data/llm_cache.sqlite, data/wikidata_cache.sqlite
# These can grow to hundreds of MB — and the data they cache is
# already in the committed JSON files under data/responses/,
# data/extractions/, etc.
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.db

# Sentence-BERT embedding cache (Phase 5 Track B; can exceed 100 MB)
data/embeddings_cache.keys.json
data/embeddings_cache.vectors.npy
*.npy
*.npz

# =============================================================
# Reference data (data/external/)
# =============================================================
# Reference CSVs (BLS prices, USDA Thrifty Plan, Compendium activities)
# are COMMITTED on purpose — they pin the exact snapshot used in
# the paper. MANIFEST.json carries SHA256s for verification.
# (No ignore rule; this comment is for clarity.)

# =============================================================
# Enriched data (data/enriched/)
# =============================================================
# Only the aggregate summary.json is committed; the 480 per-record
# enrichment JSONs are regenerable from responses + grounding scripts.
data/enriched/*
!data/enriched/summary.json

# =============================================================
# Results — per-fold ML baseline detail (low signal-to-noise)
# =============================================================
# Aggregate ml_baseline_summary*.csv files capture the headline
# numbers; the per-fold leave-one-out predictions are only useful
# when debugging the LOO loop and are regenerable from scores.csv.
results/ml_baseline_folds_affordability.csv
results/ml_baseline_folds_cultural.csv
results/ml_baseline_folds_feasibility.csv

# =============================================================
# Node / dashboard build outputs
# =============================================================
node_modules/
dashboard/dist/
dashboard/node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# =============================================================
# OS / editor cruft
# =============================================================
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*.bak
*.tmp

# =============================================================
# LaTeX build artifacts (paper/main.tex compilation outputs)
# =============================================================
paper/*.aux
paper/*.log
paper/*.out
paper/*.toc
paper/*.bbl
paper/*.blg
paper/*.synctex.gz
paper/*.fls
paper/*.fdb_latexmk
paper/*.pdf

# Exception: the progress-report PDF is the headline deliverable
# (generated by reportlab from CSVs, not a LaTeX build output).
!paper/AccessibleHealthBench_progress_report.pdf

# =============================================================
# Logs
# =============================================================
*.log
logs/

# =============================================================
# Tooling / local-only overrides
# =============================================================
.claude/
*.local.json

# =============================================================
# Archives (typically large, infrequently useful in source control)
# =============================================================
*.zip
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.tgz
*.7z
